<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I asked about this just three days ago on the easy questions megathread. Turns out it might not just be an easy question. Here&#39;s what I said back on the 15th.</p> <blockquote> <p>I just noticed that anytime I click on a login button for apps that pull up a web page displayed on the app itself instead of opening a tab on my default browser (Firefox), the app will either just close the page or just kill the app. Here&#39;s an error I get for trying to login to Google through Gnome Accounts: </p> <p>03:24:49.0736 online-accounts-cc-panel: WARNING: Error showing account: Child process killed by signal 11 </p> <p>And here&#39;s an error I get trying to login to Epic Games through Lutris: </p> <p>DEBUG 2022-07-15 03:26:41,829 [base.login:285]:Connecting to Epic Games Store </p> <p>Segmentation fault (core dumped) </p> <p>Am I missing a package or something?</p> </blockquote> <p>I also have some videos of what&#39;s going on here.</p> <p><a href="https://streamable.com/gvzlpj">https://streamable.com/gvzlpj</a></p> <p>One thing I found out is that it doesn&#39;t work on Wayland. On X11, the webpages open up.</p> <p><a href="https://streamable.com/cs1r1s">https://streamable.com/cs1r1s</a></p> <p>Again, am I missing a package?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/SomeAwesomeGuyDa69th"> /u/SomeAwesomeGuyDa69th </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w2817d/login_prompts_on_gnome_accounts_and_lutris_dont/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w2817d/login_prompts_on_gnome_accounts_and_lutris_dont/">[comments]</a></span>